headline: Electronic Arts’s (NASDAQ:EA) Q1: Beats On Revenue, Stock Soars
summary: Video game publisher Electronic Arts (NASDAQ:EA) reported revenue ahead of Wall Street’s expectations in Q1 CY2025, with sales up 6.5% year on year to $1.90 billion. The company expects next quarter’s revenue to be around $1.6 billion, coming in 10.6% above analysts’ estimates. Its GAAP profit of $0.98 per share was 8.2% above analysts’ consensus estimates.
